25/04/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Ten people were injured in the fighting among soccer fans during and after a match between Serbia-Montenegro champions Red Star and league leaders Partizan on Saturday (23 April).
Fans threw plastic seats at each other and police, and then clashed outside the stadium.
Three police officers were among those hurt.
A local hospital official said none of the injuries was life threatening.
Sixty-seven fans were arrested.
The game ended in a 1-1 draw.
(Reuters, AP, AFP - 23/04/05)
